First of all, a sketch might be useful. Since we have an isosceles triangle on our hands, let's drop a median/altitude/bisector from $B$ as well: [asy]
pair pA, pB, pC, pD, pE;
pA = (-2, 0);
pB = (0, 4.5826);
pC = (2, 0);
pD = (pB * 4 + pC * 5) / (9);
pE = (0, 0);
